.TH GAT-SHELL-INIT 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-shell-init \- emit shell integration code
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat shell\-init
.RB [ \-\-shell
.IR bash|zsh|fish ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints a shell function that wraps
.B gat
so commands which resolve a path
.RB ( new ,
.BR go ,
.BR search )
can change the parent shell's directory. A child process cannot
.B cd
its parent, so the wrapper evaluates structured shell output. Add the output to
your shell rc file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-shell " bash|zsh|fish"
Shell dialect (default
.IR bash ).
.SH EXAMPLES
For bash or zsh, add to the rc file:
.PP
.RS
.EX
eval "$(gat shell\-init \-\-shell bash)"
.EE
.RE
.PP
For fish, add to
.IR config.fish :
.PP
.RS
.EX
gat shell\-init \-\-shell fish | source
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-doctor (1)
